    • Method Detail

      • abort

        void abort(boolean reject)
           throws ConnectionException,
                  ZebraCardException
        Aborts a print job.
        Parameters:
        reject -
        • True = abort the job and send the card to the reject bin.
        • False = abort the job and hold the card in the printer's home position.
        Throws:
        ConnectionException - if the device is busy or there is a error communicating with the printer.
        ZebraCardException - if a printer error occurs.

      • getReservationStatus

        ReservationInfo getReservationStatus(int reservationToken)
                                     throws ConnectionException,
                                            ZebraCardException,
                                            ZebraIllegalArgumentException
        Queries the printer and returns the current status of the printer from the supplied reservation token.
        Parameters:
        reservationToken - printer's supplied reservation token.
        Returns:
        a ReservationInfo instance containing the status of the device reservation.
        Throws:
        ConnectionException - if the device is busy or there is a error communicating with the printer.
        ZebraCardException - if a printer error occurs.
        ZebraIllegalArgumentException - if the reservationToken is invalid.

      • readBarcodeData

        BarcodeReadInfo readBarcodeData()
                                throws ConnectionException,
                                       SettingsException,
                                       ZebraCardException,
                                       java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException
        Sends a job to the printer to scan and return the barcode data from a card.
        Returns:
        a BarcodeReadInfo instance containing the barcode type and data read from the card.
        Throws:
        ConnectionException - if the device is busy or there is a error communicating with the printer.
        SettingsException - if an error occurs while reading the barcode data.
        java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException - if the operation times out before it completes.
        ZebraCardException - if a printer error occurs.

      • printTestCard

        int printTestCard(byte imageNumber,
                int copies,
                boolean dualSided)
                  throws ConnectionException,
                         ZebraCardException,
                         ZebraIllegalArgumentException
        Prints the specified test image.
        ZMotif series 7, 8, and 9 printers only.
        Parameters:
        imageNumber - test image number.
        copies - number of copies to print.
        dualSided - true indicates the test image should be printed dual sided.
        Returns:
        the assigned job ID.
        Throws:
        ConnectionException - if the device is busy or there is a error communicating with the printer.
        ZebraCardException - if the printer model is not supported or a printer error occurs.
        ZebraIllegalArgumentException - if the imageNumber, copies, or dualSided are invalid.
